Package io.servicetalk.http.router.jersey

Class HttpJerseyRouterBuilder

java.lang.Object
io.servicetalk.http.router.jersey.HttpJerseyRouterBuilder
public final class HttpJerseyRouterBuilder extends Object
Builds an StreamingHttpService which routes requests to JAX-RS annotated classes, using Jersey as the routing engine, eg. 

 final StreamingHttpService router = new HttpJerseyRouterBuilder()
     .buildStreaming(application);

    • baseUriFunction

      public HttpJerseyRouterBuilder baseUriFunction(BiFunction<ConnectionContext,HttpRequestMetaData,String> baseUriFunction)
      Set the function used to compute the base URI for the incoming HTTP request. The computed base URI must have / as path, and no query nor fragment.
      Parameters:
      baseUriFunction - a BiFunction that computes a base URI String for the provided ConnectionContext and HttpRequestMetaData.

      this
